---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import "bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css";
---
<Layout title='Weekday Schedule for the Perno Family'>
  <main>
    <h1>Schedule</h1>
    <p>The following schedule is an approximation. Always follow the kid's signs first and foremost, but this can be a helpful guide.</p>
		
		<!-- Bootstrap Tabs -->
		<ul class="nav nav-tabs" id="scheduleTab" role="tablist">
			<li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
				<button class="nav-link" id="eliza-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#eliza" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="eliza" aria-selected="false">Eliza</button>
			</li>
			<li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
				<button class="nav-link active" id="daniel-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#daniel" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="daniel" aria-selected="true">Daniel</button>
			</li>
		</ul>
		
		<div class="tab-content" id="scheduleTabContent">
			<div class="tab-pane fade" id="eliza" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="eliza-tab">
				<table class="table">
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<th>~7:00am</th>
							<td>Wake up</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>7:30-9:30am</th>
							<td>Breakfast</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>11:00am</th>
							<td>Lunch</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>12:00-2:00pm</th>
							<td>Nap / Quiet Time</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>2:30pm</th>
							<td>Snack</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>6:00pm</th>
							<td>Dinner</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>7:00pm</th>
							<td>Story Time</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>8:00pm</th>
							<td>Bedtime</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
			
			<div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="daniel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="daniel-tab">
				<table class="table">
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<th>~7:00am</th>
							<td>Wake&nbsp;up</td>
							<td></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>8:00am-9:00am</th>
							<td>Feed</td>
							<td>6 oz. bottle</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>10:00am-1:00pm</th>
							<td>Nap</td>
							<td>can go down anytime between 10:00am and 11:00am, and will sleep for about 2 hours</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>1:00pm</th>
							<td>Feed</td>
							<td>6 oz. bottle</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>4:00pm</th>
							<td>Feed</td>
							<td>6 oz. bottle</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th>6:00pm</th>
							<td>Feed & Bed</td>
							<td>8 oz. bottle</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
				<h3>Overnight</h3>
				<p>Nothing should be in bed with him except what he's wearing (e.g. sleep sack, onesie). Anything else, like blankets or pillows, are suffocation hazards.</p>
				<p>You can expect him to wake up once or twice a night for 6 oz. feedings. Thankfully, he usually falls back asleep quickly.</p>
				<h3>Solid Foods</h3>
				<p>Unfortunately, he still is unable to eat solid foods. He gags and/or vomits it back up. He does get angry watching other people eat solids, so if we don't have baby food, we'll just give him a metal spoon that keeps him pretty happy.</p>
				<h3>Walker</h3>
				<p>He *loves* his walker, but we try to limit the time he spends in it because it can possibly delay his motor development.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
  </main>
  
  <!-- Bootstrap JS for tab functionality -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</Layout>

<style>
	h1 {
		margin: 2rem 0;
	}

	body { background-color: unset; }
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1em;
		max-width: 80ch;
	}
	.table>:not(caption)>*>* { /* overwrite bootstrap style */
		background-color: unset;
	}
	.list-unstyled {
		padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
	}
	
	/* Tab styling */
	.tab-content {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}
	
	.nav-tabs .nav-link.active {
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.text-center {
		text-align: center;
	}
	p {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}
</style>